             Blackstone Group LP  and PAI Partners
Holdings Inc. hired Goldman Sachs Group Inc. and JPMorgan Chase
& Co. to sell  United Biscuits Holdings Ltd.  in an auction worth
about 2 billion pounds ($3.1 billion), the Financial Times
 reported , citing people familiar with the situation.  
 Blackstone and PAI are examining plans to split Unitedâ€™s
operations into snack and biscuit businesses to make them more
attractive to bidders, the newspaper said.  
